 will copy the existing scaffold for this. The context mentions preparing a Forge workflow for a library issue that goes \\\"beyond the normal generated test scaffold.\\\" I’m wondering if the driver could use the existing build file. If it's updating from existing tests, do we need anything extra? It feels a bit uncertain, but I’ll think it through.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"The resolved 2.9.1 artifact has only normal transitive dependencies and needs no Docker image, but meaningful Guice proxy/AOP coverage on JDK 25 needs a module-opening JVM/native-image option.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"When tests exercise Guice CGLIB/proxy/AOP paths, configure both JVM tests and native-image builds with `--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED`. Prefer public Guice APIs for coverage; the 2.9.1 jar relocates many internal util/cglib classes to names such as `com.google.inject.internal.util.$MapMaker` and `com.google.inject.internal.cglib.proxy.$MethodProxy`, so tests copied from 2.1.7 that import the old non-`$` internal class names will not compile.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Adding `com.google.inject:guice` or other Guice artifacts to recover old internal class names would test the wrong implementation and can mask the actual `org.sonatype.sisu:sisu-guice` behavior.\",\n    \"`org.slf4j:slf4j-api` is optional in the POM and is not required for normal core Guice coverage unless tests intentionally exercise optional logging integration.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0bfb55c89f2b0c24016a4218e1d5e481968eb8e7492cd380d7\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1370, "output": 1200, "cacheRead": 22528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25098, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782716622206, "respons